<section>
    <div class=3D"container Pt(40px) Pb(70px) Pt(70px)--md Pb(90px)--md C(-=
-color-black-light-3)">
        <div class=3D"Ta(c)">
            <h2 class=3D"Mb(20px) Mt(0) Ta(c) Fz(--font-size-42)--md Fz(--f=
ont-size-30) Fw(800) Lh(--line-height-big-headings) W(9/12)--md W(11/12)--s=
m Mx(a)">What is statistical significance?            </h2>
            <p class=3D"Fz(--font-size-16) M(0) Maw(1000px) Mx(a)">Statisti=
cal significance quantifies whether a result obtained is likely due to chan=
ce or some factor of interest. You can utilize a significance calculator to=
 confidently evaluate and interpret your results. The data-driven approach =
empowers you to make informed decisions for optimization and ultimately ach=
ieve your desired outcomes.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class=3D"Bgc(--color-blue-light-7) Py(100px)--md Py(70px) C(--colo=
r-black-light-3)">
    <div class=3D"container">
        <div class=3D"Ta(c) Mb(40px) Mb(70px)--md">
            <h2 class=3D"Fz(--font-size-42)--md Lh(--line-height-big-headin=
gs) Fz(--font-size-26) Mt(0) Mb(20px) Fw(800)">Different approaches to calc=
ulate statistical significance</h2>
            <p class=3D"Fz(--font-size-16) M(0) Maw(950px) Mx(a)">The two c=
ommonly used approaches are Frequentist and Bayesian, which power different=
 test statistics calculators. Here is a brief information on each.</p>
        </div>
        <div class=3D"W(11/12)--md Mx(a)">
            <div class=3D"D(f) Flw(w) Mx(-10px)">
                <div class=3D"W(6/12)--md W(100%) P(10px) Bxz(bb)">
                    <div class=3D"H(100%) Bxz(bb) Bdrs(5px) Bgc(--color-whi=
te) P(40px) Fz(--font-size-16)">
                        <img src=3D"https://static.wingify.com/gcp/wp-conte=
nt/themes/vwo/images/new-website/significance-calculator/frequentist-icon.s=
vg" alt=3D"" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"60" height=3D"37" class=3D"H(a)"> =
                           <h3 class=3D"Fz(--font-size-20) Mt(20px) Mb(15px=
) Lh(--line-height-headings)">
                            Frequentist                            </h3>
                                <p class=3D"M(0)">Frequentist statistics in=
volves examining the frequency of events. It looks at how often something h=
appens in a given situation.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class=3D"W(6/12)--md W(100%) P(10px) Bxz(bb)">
                    <div class=3D"H(100%) Bxz(bb) Bdrs(5px) Bgc(--color-whi=
te) P(40px) Fz(--font-size-16)">
                        <img src=3D"https://static.wingify.com/gcp/wp-conte=
nt/themes/vwo/images/new-website/significance-calculator/bayesian-icon.svg"=
 alt=3D"" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"39" height=3D"39" class=3D"H(a)">    =
                        <h3 class=3D"Fz(--font-size-20) Mt(20px) Mb(15px) L=
h(--line-height-headings)">
                            Bayesian                            </h3>
                                <p class=3D"M(0)"><a target=3D"_blank" href=
=3D"https://help.vwo.com/hc/en-us/articles/360033991193-What-is-Bayesian-St=
atistics-" class=3D"C(--color-black-light-3)">Bayesian statistics</a> is al=
l about changing your opinion. It starts with an initial belief called the =
prior, which comes from domain expertise. Then, you gather evidence to supp=
ort or challenge that belief. After examining the evidence, your opinion sh=
ould be updated based on the new information you=E2=80=99ve acquired.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class=3D"container Py(100px)--md Py(70px) C(--color-black-light-3)">
    <div class=3D"Ta(c) Mb(120px)--md Mb(40px)">
      <h2 class=3D"Mt(0) Mb(20px) Ta(c) Fz(--font-size-42)--md Fz(--font-si=
ze-30)--sm Fz(--font-size-24) Fw(700) Lh(--line-height-big-headings) Fw(800=
)">How do we calculate statistical significance?</h2>
      <p class=3D"M(0) Fz(--font-size-16)">Here is how you can calculate st=
atistical significance using the Frequentist and Bayesian approaches.</p>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"D(f) Flw(w) Jc(sa) Ai(c) Fz(--font-size-16) Mb(80px)">
            <div class=3D"W(5/12)--md Mb(30px) Mb(0)--md">
                <h3 class=3D"Fz(--font-size-28)--md Lh(--line-height-headin=
gs) Fz(--font-size-26) Mb(20px) Mt(0)">Frequentist approach</h3>
                <p class=3D"M(0)">The Frequentist approach to statistical s=
ignificance is based on <span class=3D"C(#bf3178)"><strong>the p-value</str=
ong></span>. To determine the p-value using the Frequentist approach, you w=
ill need the following key pieces of information:</p>
                    <ul class=3D"Pstart(15px) My(20px)">
                        <li class=3D"Mb(10px) C(#bf3178)::m">The mean diffe=
rence between the two hypotheses</li>
                        <li class=3D"Mb(10px) C(#bf3178)::m">The standard d=
eviation of the difference between the two hypotheses</li>
                        <li class=3D"C(#bf3178)::m">The sample size of each=
 hypothesis</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class=3D"Fz(--font-size-16) M(0)">Once you have gath=
ered this necessary data, you can easily compute the p-value using a signif=
icance testing tool or significance level calculator. <strong>If the p-valu=
e you get is 0.05, the probability of the variation is 5%.</strong></p>
            </div>
            <div class=3D"W(5/12)--md">
            <img src=3D"https://static.wingify.com/gcp/wp-content/themes/vw=
o/images/new-website/significance-calculator/frequentist-approach.svg" alt=
=3D"" decoding=3D"async" class=3D"D(b) Mx(a) H(a)" width=3D"525" height=3D"=
267">            </div>
        </div>
        <div class=3D"D(f) Flw(w) Jc(sa) Ai(c) Fz(--font-size-16)">
            <div class=3D"W(5/12)--md Mb(30px) Mb(0)--md">
                <h3 class=3D"Fz(--font-size-28)--md Lh(--line-height-headin=
gs) Fz(--font-size-26) Mb(20px) Mt(0)">Bayesian Approach</h3>
                <p class=3D"M(0)">In this, you do statistical significance =
calculation through posterior probability. The posterior probability consid=
ers the available data and represents the probability of hypothesis A or B =
being true. The approach takes into account both prior beliefs and the evid=
ence observed in the data.</p>
                <p class=3D"My(20px)">To calculate the posterior probabilit=
y, Bayes' theorem is employed. Bayes' theorem is a mathematical formula tha=
t <span class=3D"C(#bf3178)"><strong>combines the prior probability of a hy=
pothesis with the likelihood of the data to derive the updated or posterior=
 probability.</strong></span></p>
                <p class=3D"Fz(--font-size-16) M(0)">A posterior <strong>pr=
obability of greater than 95%</strong> is considered to be <strong>strong e=
vidence</strong> in favor of the hypothesis.</p>
                <p class=3D"Mt(20px) Mb(0)">
                Know more about our Bayesian approach in the article series=
 we created on <a href=3D"https://help.vwo.com/hc/en-us/sections/4053128751=
3241-Enhanced-Reports" class=3D"C(#3892e3)" target=3D"blank">Bayesian A/B t=
esting at VWO.</a>                </p>
            </div>
            <div class=3D"W(5/12)--md">
            <img src=3D"https://static.wingify.com/gcp/wp-content/themes/vw=
o/images/new-website/significance-calculator/bayesian-approach.svg" alt=3D"=
" decoding=3D"async" class=3D"D(b) Mx(a) H(a)" width=3D"525" height=3D"267"=
>            </div>
        </div>
  </div>
</section>




<section class=3D"Bgc(--color-blue-light-7) C(--color-black-light-3)">
  <div class=3D"container Py(100px)--md Py(70px)">
    <div class=3D"Ta(c) Mb(100px)--xs Mb(40px)">
      <h2 class=3D"Mt(0) Mb(20px) Ta(c) Fz(--font-size-38)--md Fz(--font-si=
ze-30)--sm Fz(--font-size-24) Fw(800) Lh(--line-height-headings)">Why do we=
 use Bayesian statistics?</h2>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"D(f)--sm Flw(w) Jc(sa) Ai(c) Mb(150px)--sm Mb(100px)  Mb(=
60px) Mb(0):lc ">
    <div class=3D"W(5/12)--md W(10/12)--sm Mx(a) Mx(0)--md Ta(c) Ta(start)-=
-md">
                            <h3 class=3D"Fz(--font-size-32)--md Lh(--line-h=
eight-headings)--md Lh(n) Ta(start)--md Ta(c) Fz(--font-size-22) Mt(0) Mb(2=
0px) Fw(700)">
                Intuitive Test Reports            </h3>
                <p class=3D"Mb(10px) Ta(c) Ta(start)--md Mt(0) Fz(--font-si=
ze-18)">At VWO, we recognize that non-statistical users often misinterpret =
the frequentist p-value as a Bayesian posterior probability, which leads to=
 incorrect conclusions about the superiority of one variation over another.=
 To address this issue, we developed the industry's first Bayesian statisti=
cal engine.</p>
        <p class=3D"Mb(10px) Ta(c) Ta(start)--md Mt(0) Fz(--font-size-18)">=
Our Bayesian statistical engine provides users with easily understandable r=
esults, eliminating the risk of making mistakes while conducting A/B tests =
on revenue or other crucial key performance indicators (KPIs). By adopting =
a more intuitive approach, we ensure that our users obtain accurate insight=
s from our A/B test statistical significance calculator.</p>
        <p class=3D"Mb(20px) Ta(c) Ta(start)--md Mt(0) Fz(--font-size-18)">=
With our solution, you can have confidence in the statistical significance =
of your results, making informed decisions to optimize your testing, revenu=
e generation, and overall user experience. Say goodbye to misinterpretation=
s and embrace the power of the Bayesian A/B test calculator for reliable an=
d actionable A/B testing outcomes.</p>
            </div>
    <div class=3D"W(5/12)--md Ta(c) W(9/12)--sm">
    <picture><img src=3D"https://static.wingify.com/gcp/wp-content/themes/v=
wo/images/new-website/significance-calculator/intuitive-test-report.png?tr=
